description.narrative: Adolescent Girls' Empowerment and Well-being - Targeted PrioritiesUNICEF HQ, COs and ROs are supported to develop, implement and document at scale gender transformative interventions in and across sectors to enhance adolescent girls' well-being and empowerment in humanitarian and non-humanitarian setting, which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Learning Outcomes, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Sanitation. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Every Child an Equitable Chance in Life By 2021, UNICEF supported countries apply relevant policies, innovative approaches and evidence, to design and implement publicly and privately funded development and humanitarian interventions at scale, that give Every Child an Equitable Chance in Life
